{% doc %}
  @prompt
    CONTEXT: You are a senior UI/UX designer building a premium, ritual-based Ayurvedic wellness blog for DINVEDA. The aesthetic is "European Editorial Magazine" – calm, slow-living, and deeply intentional.
    
    GLOBAL STYLING RULES:
    
    Background Color: Always #FFF0DD (Warm Pastel Beige).
    Text & UI Color: Always #C17129 (Warm Brown).
    Finish: Matte, zero drop-shadows, zero heavy borders.
    Typography Hierarchy:
    Titles: 42px Serif (Playfair Display or Tenor Sans), 1.2 line-height.
    Subheaders: 28px Serif.
    Body Text: 18px Serif, 1.7 line-height for a spacious feel.
    Metadata (Date/Author): 12px Sans-Serif, Uppercase, 0.1em letter-spacing.
    PAGE STRUCTURE & SECTIONS:
    
    Centered Blog Hero:
    
    A large, full-width high-resolution lifestyle image.
    Below the image, a centered Category label (e.g., "RITUAL-WISSEN") in 12px Sans-Serif.
    Centered main Title in 42px Serif.
    Subtle metadata line (Author | Date | 5 Min Read) in 14px Sans-Serif.
    The Narrative Body:
    
    Max-Width: The text column must be narrow (max 720px) for premium readability.
    Use a large drop-cap (4 line height) for the very first letter of the post.
    Intersparse text with full-bleed or inset editorial images using minimalist Sans-Serif captions underneath.
    "Ritual-Tipp" Callout Block:
    
    Create a dedicated block mid-post with a white (#FFFFFF) background and 8px rounded corners.
    Include a small animal icon (e.g., a fox) and the heading "Ein kleiner Tipp vom Fuchs."
    Style the tip content in 16px Serif.
    "Das könnte dich auch interessieren" (Related Content):
    
    A clean 3-column grid at the bottom of the page.
    Each card should have a small image, a 12px category tag, and a 20px Serif title.
    No "Read More" buttons; the entire card/title should be the link.
    Newsletter Opt-in Circle:
    
    A simple, centered section before the footer.
    Headline: "Tritt unserem Kreis bei" (32px Serif).
    A single, thin border-bottom line for the email input field. No boxy buttons.
    EXPLICITLY AVOID:
    
{% enddoc %}
